subaward_description: UC DAVIS WILL COLLABORATE WITH STANFORD ON THE FOLLOWING TASKS: PHASE 1 TASK 1.2: ULTRA-HIGH PURITY I2 CELL FILLING AND SEALING. A UHV FILLING STATION FOR VAPOR CELLS WILL BE BUILT AND WILL INCLUDE CAPABILITIES FOR HIGH TEMPERATURE BAKING, RF SCRUBBING, AND CELL FILLING WITH VERY HIGH PURITY MOLECULAR IODINE. A KEY CAPABILITY OF OUR APPROACH IS MULTI-STAGE VAPOR DISTILLATION OF I2. THE I2 PRESSURE WILL BE OPTIMIZED TO ADDRESS CONFLICTING DEMANDS OF MINIMIZING PRESSURE BROADENING AND FREQUENCY OFFSETS, WHILE MAXIMIZING THE ABSORPTION OF THE PROBING LASER AND FLUORESCENCE DETECTION. ADVANCED METHODS FOR CELL SEALING WILL BE USED. DELIVERABLES WILL BE A REPORT OUTLINING THE BEST METHODS AND RESULTS, AND THE PRODUCTION OF AT LEAST SIX I2 VAPOR CELLS WILL BE PRODUCED THAT CAN MEET ACES PROGRAM METRICS FOR HIGH TEMPERATURE OPERATION AND LONG-TERM FREQUENCY STABILITY. MONTHS: 1-12 STANFORD 70%, UC DAVIS 30% TASK 1.3: I2 CELL CHARACTERIZATION. INITIAL MEASUREMENTS OF THE SATURATED ABSORPTION LINEWIDTH AND CONTRAST OF THE TINY I2 VAPOR CELLS FABRICATED IN TASK 1.2 WILL BE CARRIED OUT AND COMPARED THEORY SUPPORTING STABILITY GOALS. DELIVERABLES WILL BE A REPORT DETAILING THE RESULTS. MONTHS: 4-12 STANFORD 0%, UC DAVIS 100% TASK 1.5: CONSTRUCTION OF A COMPACT SATURATION SPECTROMETER WITH REPLACEABLE CELLS. WE WILL CONSTRUCT A COMPACT SPECTROMETER FOR STUDYING ALL PHASES OF THE I2 VAPOR CELL DEVELOPMENT. THIS ESSENTIAL INSTRUMENT WILL BE ASSEMBLED FROM A COMMERCIAL, TUNABLE, NARROW-LINEWIDTH, FREQUENCY-DOUBLED (532 NM) ND:YAG LASER, FOCUSING AND ISOLATION OPTICS, PHOTODETECTORS AND A LOCK-IN AMPLIFIER FOR THIRD-DERIVATIVE SPECTROSCOPY. WE WILL ALSO DEVELOP CUSTOM SERVOS FOR LOCKING THE LASER TO SATURATED ABSORPTION LINES. DELIVERABLES WILL INCLUDE SYSTEM DESIGN, PERFORMANCE CHARACTERIZATION AND RESULTS FROM SPECTROSCOPIC EVALUATIONS OF VARIOUS I2 CELLS. MONTHS: 3-5 STANFORD 40%, UC DAVIS 60% TASK 1.8: DEMONSTRATE FREQUENCY RETRACE ΔY < 10-11 AND AGING < 10-12 /DAY. WE WILL MEASURE THE FREQUENCY RETRACE (ON/OFF/ON 4/24/4 HOURS) AND AGING RATE OF THE I2 GREEN FREQUENCY STANDARD TO VERIFY THAT THE SYSTEM AND APPROACH CAN ACHIEVE THE REQUIRED ENVIRONMENTAL INSENSITIVITY ON DAY TIME SCALES (105S). MEASUREMENTS RESULTS WILL DETERMINE THE REQUIREMENTS FOR THE CONTROL SYSTEMS. WHEN PROJECTED TO LONG TIMES THE PERFORMANCE MUST BE COMMENSURATE WITH THE ULTIMATE STABILITY GOAL OF ΔY=10-13 AT ONE MONTH, WHICH WILL BE DEMONSTRATED IN PHASE-II. MONTHS: 7-12 STANFORD 80%, UC DAVIS 20% PHASE 2 TASK 2.4: SEMI-MONOLITHIC HYBRID INTEGRATION OF I2 CELL OPTICS AND DETECTORS. WE WILL DESIGN AND FABRICATE A SEMI-MONOLITHIC INTEGRATION OF THE MINIATURE VAPOR CELL, OPTICS AND DETECTION ELECTRONICS TO ENSURE THERMO-MECHANICAL STABILITY IN A SOLID STRUCTURE THAT MITIGATES NUMEROUS EFFECTS AND TECHNICAL LIMITATIONS RELATED TO THERMALLY-DRIVEN CHANGES IN GEOMETRY. SUCH EFFECTS INCLUDE OPTICAL INTERFERENCE, SCATTERED LIGHT, BEAM MISALIGNMENT, POLARIZATION AND CHANGES DETECTOR PERFORMANCE. THE HYBRID INTEGRATED I2 SYSTEM WILL BE SMALL ENOUGH THAT IT CAN MEET ACES SWAP REQUIREMENTS IN FUTURE INTEGRATION INTO COMPLETE CLOCK. MONTHS: 6-12 STANFORD 40%, UC DAVIS 60% TASK 2.5: IMPLEMENT CONTROL SYSTEMS. MEASUREMENTS FROM PHASE-I WILL GUIDE THE DESIGN OF CONTROL SYSTEMS THAT ARE REQUIRED TO MITIGATE RESIDUAL FREQUENCY SHIFTS THAT DEPEND UPON CONTROLLABLE ENVIRONMENTAL FACTORS INCLUDING: TEMPERATURE, OPTICAL POWER, BEAM GEOMETRY, LASER AM AND FM NOISE, MODULATION AND DETECTION METHODS, RESIDUAL AMPLITUDE MODULATION, AND ELECTRONIC PHASE SHIFTS. DELIVERABLES WILL INCLUDE DATA CHARACTERIZING THE VARIATIONS, CONTROL STRATEGIES TO AMELIORATE THEM AND CIRCUIT DESIGNS AND VERIFICATIONS. MONTHS: 7-12 STANFORD 25%, UC DAVIS 75% TASK 2.6: CELL AGING TESTS AND COMPENSATION. FREQUENCY CHANGES OVER TIME ARE COMMONLY OBSERVED IN ATOMIC FREQUENCY REFERENCES, PARTICULARLY VAPOR CELL SYSTEMS. HOWEVER, BASED ON DECADES OF WORK ON I2 CELLS FOR FREQUENCY AND LENGTH METROLOGY THE HIGHEST QUALITY

prime_award_cfda_numbers_and_titles: 12.800: AIR FORCE DEFENSE RESEARCH SCIENCES PROGRAM
subawardee_business_types: OTHER NOT FOR PROFIT ORGANIZATION,1862 LAND GRANT COLLEGE,EDUCATIONAL INSTITUTION,VETERINARY COLLEGE
subaward_description:
IN CONJUNCTION WITH PARTNERS UNIVERSITY OF CALIFORNIA, SANTA BARBARA ("UCSB"), CISCO SYSTEMS, INC. ("CISCO"),
 COLUMBIA UNIVERSITY ("COLUMBIA"), KEYSIGHT TECHNOLOGIES, INC. ("KEYSIGHT"), LOCKHEED MARTIN
 ("LOCKHEED"), UNIVERSITY OF CALIFORNIA, DAVIS ("UCD") WILL DO CONDUCT A PROJECT ENTITLED "HIGH CAPACITY PHOTONIC INTERCONNECTED SYSTEMS."
 THE LAST DECADE HAS SEEN A LARGE PART OF THE DIGITAL WORLD SHIFTED INTO THE CLOUD AND THE PROLIFERATION OF DATACENTERS. THE TYPICAL DATACENTER SIZE HAS ALSO SOARED: MOST RECENT HYPERSCALE
 DATACENTERS CONTAIN HUNDREDS OF THOUSANDS OF SERVERS. THESE MANY SERVERS PROCESS DATA, BUT ALSO RECEIVE AND EXCHANGE MASSIVE AMOUNTS OF INFORMATION. DATA COMMUNICATIONS WITHIN DATA CENTERS EXCEEDS BY OVER AN ORDER OF MAGNITUDE THE TOTAL AMOUNT OF DATA TRANSITING OVER THE INTERNET. ALREADY TODAY, A MAJOR STRESS IS PLACED ONTO DIN. DINS, HOWEVER, MIGHT BE YET UNDER HIGHER PRESSURE WITH THE EMERGENCE OF NOVEL CLOUD DATA ANALYTICS APPLICATIONS RELYING ON MACHINE AND DEEP LEARNING TECHNIQUES. THESE TECHNIQUES, USED FOR EXAMPLE IN STREAMING VIDEO OBJECT RECOGNITION, INVOLVE MASSIVELY PARALLEL PROCESSING UNITS (GPU) AND MANYCORE (CPU) PROCESSORS FURTHER PUSHING THE LIMITS ON CURRENT DIN ARCHITECTURES AND MEMORY-TO-CPU/GPU LINKS. IN THIS NEW CONTEXT WHERE COMPUTE INFRASTRUCTURES ARE PREDOMINANTLY LIMITED BY THE
 ABILITY TO EFFICIENTLY MOVE DATA OVER ANY DISTANCE, IT IS CRUCIAL TO IMPROVE ENERGY AND COST EFFICIENCIES OF COMMUNICATIONS SYSTEMS. THIS PROJECT AIMS AT DEVELOPING A PLATFORM IN AIM PHOTONICS TO PROVIDE SUCH HIGH COST AND ENERGY EFFICIENT OPTICAL LINKS AND FABRICS, ABLE TO THOROUGHLY CATER FOR FUTURE DATACOM REQUIREMENTS. THIS PROJECT TARGETS INNOVATION IN MANUFACTURING OF INTEGRATED SILICON PHOTONICS DIES FOR ULTRAHIGH SPEED TRANSCEIVERS, THE REALIZATION OF PHOTONIC LINKS SEAMLESSLY INTEGRATED WITH CONVENTIONAL COMPUTER CHIPS AS CPU, GPU AND MEMORY MODULES, AND INTEGRATED SILICON PHOTONIC SWITCHES ALLOWING BANDWIDTH TO BE STEERED ON DEMAND AMONG DIVERSE RESOURCES. HIGH CAPACITY, COST AND ENERGY EFFICIENCY PHOTONIC INTERCONNECTED SYSTEMS REQUIRE DENSE FABRICATION PROCESSES WITH HIGH YIELD, PHOTONIC INTERPOSERS AND INTEGRATION FOR OPTOELECTRONIC INTEGRATION AND PACKAGING, AND AUTOMATED CHARACTERIZATION AND FUNCTIONAL TESTING. THIS PROJECT
 THUS COMPREHENSIVELY EXERCISES AND CHALLENGES THE CAPABILITIES OF AIM PHOTONICS.

prime_award_cfda_numbers_and_titles: 12.351: SCIENTIFIC RESEARCH - COMBATING WEAPONS OF MASS DESTRUCTION
subawardee_business_types: OTHER NOT FOR PROFIT ORGANIZATION,1862 LAND GRANT COLLEGE,EDUCATIONAL INSTITUTION,VETERINARY COLLEGE
subaward_description:
DIRECT NUMERICAL SIMULATION OF THE RT/RM INSTABILITY CAN BE PROHIBITIVELY EXPENSIVE, SO DEVELOPING A RANGE OF LOW-TO-HIGH FIDELITY MODELS TO PREDICT FLUID INTERFACE LOCATION, SHAPE, GROWTH, AND FLUID MIXING IS OF PARAMOUNT IMPORTANCE. THERE HAVE BEEN A NUMBER OF ATTEMPTS TO MODEL THE GROWTH OF SPIKES AND BUBBLES IN FAIRLY GENERAL SETTINGS, IN WHICH A VARIETY OF SIMPLIFYING ASSUMPTIONS ARE MADE TO THE EULER EQUATIONS OF FLUID MECHANICS, THAT ARE HOPED TO CAPTURE THE ZEROTH ORDER PHYSICS CORRECTLY, AND PERMIT THE DYNAMICS TO BE DESCRIBED BY ORDINARY DIFFERENTIAL EQUATIONS.
 
 THE PROPOSED EFFORT AT UC DAVIS IS FOCUSED ON THE DEVELOPMENT OF A HIERARCHY OF LOW-TO-HIGH FIDELITY FAST-RUNNING MODELS OF FLUID INTERFACE MOTION AND MIXING, DESIGNED FOR CONDITIONS INVOLVING COMPRESSIBLE MULTI-PHASE FLOWS SPECIFIC TO NUCLEAR WEAPON EFFECTS. THE PROPOSED MODELS ARE WELL-POSED, HIGHLY STABLE, AND ACCURATELY PREDICT QUALITATIVE AND QUANTITATIVE FEATURES OF THE INTERFACE LOCATION AND FLUID MIXING.

prime_awardee_name: NORTHERN CALIFORNIA INSTITUTE FOR RESEARCH AN
prime_awardee_business_types: Nonprofit with 501C3 IRS Status (Other then Institution of Higher Education)
prime_award_base_transaction_description: Effects of Traumatic Brain Injury and Posttraumatic Stress Disorder on Alzheimers Disease
subawardee_business_types: OTHER NOT FOR PROFIT ORGANIZATION,1862 LAND GRANT COLLEGE,EDUCATIONAL INSTITUTION,VETERINARY COLLEGE
subaward_description: DR. DECARLI WILL SUPERVISE CALCULATION OF MEASURES OF WHITE MATTER DISEASE BURDEN USING OUR VALIDATED, FULLY-AUTOMATED WMH DETECTION METHOD AS PREVIOUSLY DESCRIBED (SCHWARZ, FLETCHER ET AL. 2009) AND RECENTLY OPTIMIZED FOR FLAIR IMAGING. IN ADDITION, DR. DECARLI WILL SUPERVISE A TRAINED AND VALIDATED EXPERT WHO WILL DETERMINE THE GROSS LOCATIONS, SIZES, AND ETIOLOGIES OF MRI-EVIDENT INFARCTS USING THE SAME RELIABLE, REPEATABLE PROTOCOL THAT HAS BEEN USED FOR ADNI AND A VARIETY OF OTHER STUDIES, INCLUDING THE FRAMINGHAM HEART STUDY.

prime_awardee_name: NORTHERN CALIFORNIA INSTITUTE FOR RESEARCH AN
prime_awardee_business_types: Nonprofit with 501C3 IRS Status (Other then Institution of Higher Education)
prime_award_base_transaction_description: Effects of Traumatic Brain Injury and Posttraumatic Stress Disorder on Alzheimers Disease
subawardee_business_types: OTHER NOT FOR PROFIT ORGANIZATION,1862 LAND GRANT COLLEGE,EDUCATIONAL INSTITUTION,VETERINARY COLLEGE
subaward_description: THE BIOSTATISTICS CORE WILL WORK CLOSELY WITH CO-INVESTIGATORS TO ADDRESS THE SPECIFIC HYPOTHESES OF THE PROPOSAL. PRIMARY ANALYSES INVOLVE COMPARING GROUPS ON BASELINE LEVELS OF CSF, NEUROIMAGING (MRI AND AMYLOID PET), AND COGNITIVE MEASURES ASSOCIATED WITH AD PATHOLOGY AND ANNUAL CHANGE IN MRI AND COGNITIVE MEASURES TO ASSESS WHETHER PTSD OR TBI IS ASSOCIATED WITH INCREASED EVIDENCE FOR AD IN VETERANS WITH MCI COMPARED TO VETERANS WITH MCI BUT WITHOUT PTSD OR TBI. FURTHER ANALYSES WILL FOCUS ON WITHIN GROUP I CORRELATIONS TO ASSESS A DOSE-RESPONSE ASSOCIATION BETWEEN OUTCOMES AND SEVERITY OF PTSD OR TBI AND WHETHER TBI OR PTSD REDUCES COGNITIVE RESERVE. ADDITIONAL EXPLORATORY ANALYSES WILL ALSO BE CONDUCTED.

prime_award_base_transaction_description: Effects of Traumatic Brain Injury and Posttraumatic Stress Disorder on Alzheimers Disease
subawardee_business_types: OTHER NOT FOR PROFIT ORGANIZATION,1862 LAND GRANT COLLEGE,EDUCATIONAL INSTITUTION,VETERINARY COLLEGE
subaward_description: THE BIOSTATISTICS CORE WILL WORK CLOSELY WITH CO-INVESTIGATORS TO ADDRESS THE SPECIFIC HYPOTHESES OF THE PROPOSAL. PRIMARY ANALYSES INVOLVE COMPARING GROUPS ON BASELINE LEVELS OF CSF, NEUROIMAGING (MRI AND AMYLOID PET), AND COGNITIVE MEASURES ASSOCIATED WITH AD PATHOLOGY AND ANNUAL CHANGE IN MRI AND COGNITIVE MEASURES TO ASSESS WHETHER PTSD OR TBI IS ASSOCIATED WITH INCREASED EVIDENCE FOR AD IN VETERANS WITH MCI COMPARED TO VETERANS WITH MCI BUT WITHOUT PTSD OR TBI. FURTHER ANALYSES WILL FOCUS ON WITHIN GROUP I CORRELATIONS TO ASSESS A DOSE-RESPONSE ASSOCIATION BETWEEN OUTCOMES AND SEVERITY OF PTSD OR TBI AND WHETHER TBI OR PTSD REDUCES COGNITIVE RESERVE. ADDITIONAL EXPLORATORY ANALYSES WILL ALSO BE CONDUCTED.

prime_award_base_transaction_description: TAS::97 040000::TAS  INTEGRATED PHOTONICS IMI
prime_award_cfda_numbers_and_titles: 12.800: AIR FORCE DEFENSE RESEARCH SCIENCES PROGRAM
subawardee_business_types: OTHER NOT FOR PROFIT ORGANIZATION,1862 LAND GRANT COLLEGE,EDUCATIONAL INSTITUTION,VETERINARY COLLEGE
subaward_description:
1) "HIGH CAPACITY HIGH RADIX OPTICAL SWITCH"THIS PROJECT WILL BE ABLE TO PROVIDE PHOTONIC SWITCHING ARCHITECTURES FOR A MULTITUDE OF HIGH
 PERFORMANCE COMPUTING PLATFORMS TO MEET TWO CRITICAL REQUIREMENTS: (1) HIGH-SPEED SWITCHING FOR BANDWIDTH-DENSE CHANNELS (TB/S), AND (2) HIGH-RADIX CONNECTIVITY FOR FINE-GRANULARITY END-POINTS
 ACROSS MANY CHANNELS. TWO MAJOR PHOTONIC FUNCTIONALITIES, OR PRIMITIVES, CAN BE USED TO MEET THESE
 REQUIREMENTS: OPTICAL SPATIAL SWITCHING AND WAVELENGTH SELECTIVITY. THIS PROJECT WILL BE A KEY DEMONSTRATOR OF THE POWER AND QUALITY OF PHOTONIC INTEGRATION. IT IS IMPOSSIBLE WITHOUT INTEGRATION OF HUNDREDS OF DEVICES IN THE FIRST DEMONSTRATION AND THOUSANDS IN
 SUBSEQUENT YEARS. AN 8X8 OPTICAL SWITCH WITH THE CAPABILITY OF DROPPING TWO WAVELENGTHS AT EACH CROSSPOINT REQUIRES AT LEAST 128 DEVICES, AND PROBABLY 256 TO ALLOW FOR MONITORING OF THE SWITCH AT
 INTERMEDIATE POINTS. IT WILL PROVIDE FEEDBACK TO THE EPDA TEAM AS THE SPREAD IN PERFORMANCE OF NOMINALLY IDENTICAL DEVICES WILL BE CHARACTERIZED. THE LARGE NUMBER OF OPTICAL INPUT/OUTPUT ("1/0") (INITIALLY 8 FIBERS, BUT SOON 128 FIBERS) WILL DRIVE THE OPTICAL PACKAGING TECHNOLOGY. THE INTEGRATION OF
 ELECTRONIC DRIVERS AND MONITORS IS A GOOD TEST OF THE 3D STACKING TECHNOLOGY AND EPDA MODELS FOR THEIR PERFORMANCE. SCALING THIS STRUCTURE TO LARGER SIZES REQUIRES OPTICAL GAIN TO BE INCORPORATED, WHICH IS PLANNED IN LATER YEARS. 
 (2) "EDWFD" THE PROJECT PARTICIPANTS WILL PROVIDE THE UNIFIED KNOWLEDGE, TECHNOLOGY AND WORKFORCE INTERFACE FOR AIM PHOTONICS. SUCCESS FOR AIM ACADEMY WILL BE ACHIEVED THROUGH FIVE COORDINATED STRATEGIC ACTIVITIES:
   EDUCATION: CREATION AND DISSEMINATION OF SCALABLE, STACKABLE INSTRUCTIONAL RESOURCES AND RESEARCH EXPERIENCES THAT PREPARE STUDENTS AND INTEGRATED PHOTONICS TECHNICIANS, ENGINEERS AND RESEARCHERS TO BUILD PRODUCTIVE CAREERS AND A STRONG U.S. INDUSTRY.
   WORKFORCE DEVELOPMENT: IDENTIFY SKILLS GAPS AND EMPLOYMENT NEEDS, CREATE ACCESSIBLE PATHWAYS FOR STUDENTS AND PROFESSIONALS TO ACTIVELY ENGAGE IN TECHNICAL AND PROFESSIONAL SKILLS TRAINING DEVELOPED TO MEET CURRENT AND FUTURE INTEGRATED PHOTONICS WORKFORCE DEMANDS.
   ROADMAP: TO COORDINATE AND ARCHIVE KNOWLEDGE AND TECHNOLOGY CREATION AMONG THE AIM PHOTONICS PROJECTS WITH AN INTEGRATED PHOTONICS TECHNOLOGY ROADMAP THAT BUILDS A COHERENT COHORT AMONG AIM PHOTONICS AND THE INDUSTRY WORKFORCES; DEFINES THE DIFFICULT TECHNOLOGY CHALLENGES; AND CREATES THE POTENTIAL SOLUTIONS FOR GROWTH OF THE INDUSTRY.
   ASSESSMENT: METRICS WILL BE APPLIED TO ASSESS PROGRESS AND OUTCOMES ON THE OBJECTIVES OF CREATING COMMUNITIES OF PRACTICE IN MANUFACTURING BY MAKING THE TRADITIONAL EDUCATION SYSTEM MORE RESPONSIVE TO THE DEMAND FOR WORKFORCE SKILLS, BUILDING THE INDUSTRY-ACADEMIC PARTNERSHIP AND APPRENTICESHIP PROGRAMS FOR STUDENTS, AND PROGRAMS FOR WORKERS TO EXPAND THEIR SKILL SETS FOR THE INTEGRATED PHOTONICS MANUFACTURING SECTOR.
   PROGRAM SUPPORT, MANAGEMENT, AND COORDINATION: CREATE THE PERSONNEL AND TECHNOLOGY COMPETENCES THAT SUPPORT EMERGENCE OF THE AIM PHOTONICS INTEGRATED PHOTONICS MANUFACTURING PLATFORM AND ITS U.S. COMMERCIAL SUCCESS, AND REPRESENT AIM ACADEMY TO AIM PHOTONICS, NATIONAL NETWORK FOR MANUFACTURING INNOVATION ("NNMI") AND INTEGRATED PHOTONICS MANUFACTURING (" IPM" ) COMMUNITY CONSTITUENCIES. LEAD DEVELOPMENT OF EDUCATION FACTORY FACILITIES. INTERFACE WITH OTHER MANUFACTURING INSTITUTES IN EDUCATION AND WORKFORCE PROGRAMS.
 (3)"HIGH CAPACITY PHOTONIC INTERCONNECTED SYSTEMS" THE PROJECT ADDRESSES TWO OF THE MOST SIGNIFICANT CHALLENGES FOR DATACENTERS AND MORE BROADLY FOR DATACOM SYSTEMS - HIGH-CAPACITY COMMUNICATIONS AND HIGH EFFICIENCY SWITCHING. THE TECHNOLOGY TO BE
 DEVELOPED UNDER THIS PROJECT WILL SERVE AS A BASIS FOR ARCHITECTURAL EVOLUTION OF DATACOM SYSTEMS, MOST NOTABLY BY REDUCING THE ENERGY FOOTPRINT OF POWER-HUNGRY ELECTRONICS, BRINGING PHOTONICS CLOSER TO
 ELECTRONICS, AS WELL AS ADDING VALUABLE FUNCTIONALITY NATURALLY OFFERED BY INTEGRATED PHOTONICS.

prime_award_base_transaction_description: EFFECTS OF TRAUMATIC BRAIN INJURY AND POST-TRAUMATIC STRESS DISORDER AND ALZHEIMERS DISEASE ON BRAIN TAU IN VIETNAM VETERANS USING ADNI. THE PURPOSE OF THIS MODIFICATION IS TO INCORPORATE BY REFERENCE, THE REVISED BUDGET DATED 31 AUGUST 2016 AND THE REVISED SOW, DATED 16 NOVEMBER 2016, PER THE RECIPIENT'S REQUEST DATED 16 NOVEMBER 2016. NO FURTHER REDUCTIONS IN PATIENT NUMBERS IN THE SOW WILL BE ALLOWED. SEE SUMMARY OF CHANGES.
subawardee_business_types: OTHER NOT FOR PROFIT ORGANIZATION,1862 LAND GRANT COLLEGE,EDUCATIONAL INSTITUTION,VETERINARY COLLEGE
subaward_description: THE OVERALL GOAL OF THIS PROJECT IS TO DETERMINE THE EFFECTS OF PRIOR TRAUMATIC BRAIN INJURY (TBI), AND ONGOING POST-TRAUMATIC STRESS DISORDER ON BRAIN TAU, AND THE LONGITUDINAL CHANGE OF BRAIN TAU, MEASURED WITH THE TAU SPECIFIC LIGAND T807 AND POSITRON EMISSION TOMOGRAPHY (PET) SCANNING.  CONSIDERABLE EVIDENCE SUGGESTS THAT, WHILE BRAIN Aβ MIGHT PRECIPITATE COGNITIVE DECLINE IN AGING, THE ACTUAL SEVERITY OF THE DECLINE IS MORE CLOSELY LINKED TO DEPOSITION OF BRAIN TAU.  FURTHERMORE, TAU IS DEPOSITED IN CASES OF SINGLE TBI AND PATIENTS WITH CHRONIC TRAUMATIC ENCEPHALOPATHY (CTE). TOGETHER, THESE FINDINGS SUGGEST THAT TBI MIGHT EXACERBATE Aβ-RELATED DEPOSITION OF TAU AND THAT THE TAU WILL BE STRONGLY LINKED TO COGNITIVE DECLINE.

prime_award_cfda_numbers_and_titles: 12.351: SCIENTIFIC RESEARCH - COMBATING WEAPONS OF MASS DESTRUCTION
subawardee_business_types: OTHER NOT FOR PROFIT ORGANIZATION,1862 LAND GRANT COLLEGE,EDUCATIONAL INSTITUTION,VETERINARY COLLEGE
subaward_description:
DIRECT NUMERICAL SIMULATION OF THE RT/RM INSTABILITY CAN BE PROHIBITIVELY EXPENSIVE, SO DEVELOPING A RANGE OF LOW-TO-HIGH FIDELITY MODELS TO PREDICT FLUID INTERFACE LOCATION, SHAPE, GROWTH, AND FLUID MIXING IS OF PARAMOUNT IMPORTANCE. THERE HAVE BEEN A NUMBER OF ATTEMPTS TO MODEL THE GROWTH OF SPIKES AND BUBBLES IN FAIRLY GENERAL SETTINGS, IN WHICH A VARIETY OF SIMPLIFYING ASSUMPTIONS ARE MADE TO THE EULER EQUATIONS OF FLUID MECHANICS, THAT ARE HOPED TO CAPTURE THE ZEROTH ORDER PHYSICS CORRECTLY, AND PERMIT THE DYNAMICS TO BE DESCRIBED BY ORDINARY DIFFERENTIAL EQUATIONS.
 
 THE PROPOSED EFFORT AT UC DAVIS IS FOCUSED ON THE DEVELOPMENT OF A HIERARCHY OF LOW-TO-HIGH FIDELITY FAST-RUNNING MODELS OF FLUID INTERFACE MOTION AND MIXING, DESIGNED FOR CONDITIONS INVOLVING COMPRESSIBLE MULTI-PHASE FLOWS SPECIFIC TO NUCLEAR WEAPON EFFECTS. THE PROPOSED MODELS ARE WELL-POSED, HIGHLY STABLE, AND ACCURATELY PREDICT QUALITATIVE AND QUANTITATIVE FEATURES OF THE INTERFACE LOCATION AND FLUID MIXING.

prime_award_base_transaction_description: A FETUS-TARGETED ANTIBODY THERAPY TO PREVENT ZIKA VIRUS INFECTION DURING PREGNANCY
subawardee_business_types: OTHER NOT FOR PROFIT ORGANIZATION,1862 LAND GRANT COLLEGE,EDUCATIONAL INSTITUTION,VETERINARY COLLEGE
subaward_description:
ZIKA VIRUS (ZIKV) INFECTION OF PREGNANT WOMEN IS ASSOCIATED WITH A RISK OF MICROCEPHALY
 AND OTHER CONGENITAL BIRTH DEFECTS IN THEIR INFANTS, THE SO-CALLED CONGENITAL ZIKA
 SYNDROME. THERE IS CURRENTLY NO LICENSED VACCINE TO PREVENT ZIKA VIRUS (ZIKV).
 THEREFORE, THERE IS AN URGENT NEED FOR INTERVENTIONS THAT CAN PROTECT PEOPLE AT RISK,
 PARTICULARLY PREGNANT WOMEN AND THEIR FETUSES. ZIKV INFECTION OF RHESUS MACAQUES HAS
 BEEN DEMONSTRATED TO BE USEFUL ANIMAL MODEL TO STUDY PATHOGENESIS AND PROVIDE PROOFOF-
 CONCEPT OF ANTIVIRAL INTERVENTIONS.
 THE ADMINISTRATION OF NEUTRALIZING ANTIBODIES AGAINST ZIKA VIRUS DURING PREGNANCY HAS
 THE POTENTIAL TO BE EFFECTIVE IN PROTECTING THE FETUS AGAINST INFECTION, OR IN REDUCING VIRUS
 REPLICATION IF THE FETUS IS ALREADY INFECTED. HOWEVER, THERE ARE GAPS IN OUR KNOWLEDGE OF
 THE TRANSPLACENTAL TRANSFER OF SUCH ANTIBODIES LATE IN PREGNANCY. THE PROPOSED STUDIES
 ARE AIMED AT STUDYING THE TRANSPLACENTAL TRANSFER OF SUCH ANTI-ZIKA ANTIBODIES IN THE
 PREGNANT RHESUS MACAQUE MODEL. FOUR PREGNANT ANIMALS WILL BE ADMINISTERED
 ANTIBODIES APPROXIMATELY 2 WEEKS PRIOR TO C-SECTION. AT TIME OF C-SECTION, MATERNAL
 BLOOD AND CORD BLOOD WILL BE COLLECTED TO DETERMINE ANTIBODY LEVELS IN BOTH
 COMPARTMENTS.
 THE EXPERIMENTS WILL BE PERFORMED AT THE CALIFORNIA NATIONAL PRIMATE RESEARCH CENTER.
 DR. VAN ROMPAY AND THE CNPRC STAFF WILL BE RESPONSIBLE TO PERFORM ALL NONHUMAN
 PRIMATE EXPERIMENTS. THIS INCLUDES ALL THE REGULATORY PROCEDURES (IACUC, ANIMAL
 SCHEDULES), EXPERIMENTAL PROCEDURES (ANTIBODY ADMINISTRATIONS), COORDINATION OF SAMPLE
 COLLECTION AND C-SECTION), AND SAMPLE STORAGE & SHIPMENT.

prime_award_base_transaction_description: Effects of Traumatic Brain Injury and Post Traumatic Stress Disorder and Alzheimer's Disease on Brain Tau in vietnam Veterans using ADNI
subawardee_business_types: OTHER NOT FOR PROFIT ORGANIZATION,1862 LAND GRANT COLLEGE,EDUCATIONAL INSTITUTION,VETERINARY COLLEGE
subaward_description: THE OVERALL GOAL OF THIS PROJECT IS TO DETERMINE THE EFFECTS OF PRIOR TRAUMATIC BRAIN INJURY (TBI), AND ONGOING POST-TRAUMATIC STRESS DISORDER ON BRAIN TAU, AND THE LONGITUDINAL CHANGE OF BRAIN TAU, MEASURED WITH THE TAU SPECIFIC LIGAND T807 AND POSITRON EMISSION TOMOGRAPHY (PET) SCANNING.  CONSIDERABLE EVIDENCE SUGGESTS THAT, WHILE BRAIN Aβ MIGHT PRECIPITATE COGNITIVE DECLINE IN AGING, THE ACTUAL SEVERITY OF THE DECLINE IS MORE CLOSELY LINKED TO DEPOSITION OF BRAIN TAU.  FURTHERMORE, TAU IS DEPOSITED IN CASES OF SINGLE TBI AND PATIENTS WITH CHRONIC TRAUMATIC ENCEPHALOPATHY (CTE). TOGETHER, THESE FINDINGS SUGGEST THAT TBI MIGHT EXACERBATE Aβ-RELATED DEPOSITION OF TAU AND THAT THE TAU WILL BE STRONGLY LINKED TO COGNITIVE DECLINE.

subaward_description: DR. DECARLI WILL SUPERVISE CALCULATION OF MEASURES OF WHITE MATTER DISEASE BURDEN USING OUR VALIDATED, FULLY AUTOMATED WMH DETECTION METHOD AS PREVIOUSLY DESCRIBED (SCHWARZ, FLETCHER ET AL. 2009) AND RECENTLY OPTIMIZED FOR FLAIR IMAGING. IN ADDITION, DR. DECARLI WILL SUPERVISE A TRAINED AND VALIDATED EXPERT WILL DETERMINE THE GROSS LOCATIONS, SIZES, AND ETIOLOGIES OF MRI-EVIDENT INFARCTS AND INTENSITY ABNORMALITIES CONSISTENT WITH CLOSED HEAD INJURY USING THE SAME RELIABLE, REPEATABLE PROTOCOL THAT HAS BEEN USED FOR ADNI AND A VARIETY OF OTHER STUDIES, INCLUDING THE FRAMINGHAM HEART STUDY.

prime_award_base_transaction_description: DIAGNOSIS EVALUATION AND TREATMENT OF COMBAT TRAUMATIC BRAIN INJURY AND POLYTRAUMA
prime_award_cfda_numbers_and_titles: 12.750: UNIFORMED SERVICES UNIVERSITY MEDICAL RESEARCH PROJECTS
subawardee_business_types: OTHER NOT FOR PROFIT ORGANIZATION,1862 LAND GRANT COLLEGE,EDUCATIONAL INSTITUTION,VETERINARY COLLEGE
subaward_description:
OUR PRIME AWARD INCORPORATES GOAL NUMBER THREE (3) ENTITLED "BLAST TBI EXPOSURE LIMITS: DEVELOPMENT OF OCCUPATIONAL EXPOSURE LIMITS GOVERNING EXPOSURE TO MULTIPLE BLAST EVENTS .  THIS IS A MULTI-CENTER COLLABORATIVE EFFORT AIMED AT THE KNOWLEDGE GAP REGARDING SAFE EXPOSURE LIMITS FOR THE BRAIN IN TROOPS EXPOSED TO MULTIPLE BLAST EVENTS. WE ARE COLLABORATING WITH THE UNIVERSITY OF CALIFORNIA-DAVIS (UC DAVIS) ON SOME OF THE PARALLEL WORK THAT WE ARE FUNDING WITH THE UNIFORMED SERVICES UNIVERSITY OF THE HEALTH SCIENCES (USUHS) INVOLVING THE DEVELOPMENT OF ALGORITHMS FOR MEASURING SMALL WORLD CONNECTIVITY IN ADNI DOD DATASETS.  WHILE USUHS INVESTIGATOR DR. RAPP'S GROUP IS PRIMARILY FOCUSED ON THE DEVELOPMENT OF THESE ALGORITHMS IN A MEG SETTING, WE ARE COLLABORATING WITH UC DAVIS TO LOOK AT SMALL WORLD CONNECTIVITY UNDER RESTING STATE CONDITIONS AND ANALYZING OPEN SOURCE DATA (I.E., ADNI-DOD). 
 
 THE DAVIDSON LAB HAS CREATED A PIPELINE TO CREATE GRAPHS FROM FMRI IMAGING OF THE ADNI DOD DATA SET. THIS DATA SET AS OF TODAY CONTAINS 12 PTSD, 10 TBI, 23 CONTROL AND 9 PTSD AND TBI DIAGNOSED VIETNAM VETERANS. EVENTUALLY THIS ONGOING STUDY AIMS TO HAVE 85 OF EACH POPULATION. SEE (HTTP://ADNI.LONI.USC.EDU/STUDY- DESIGN/COLLABORATIVE-STUDIES/DOD-ADNI/) FOR DETAILS.
 PRELIMINARY WORK INDICATES A DIFFERENCE BETWEEN THE GRAPHS OF TWO POPULATIONS (PTSD AND CONTROL) IN TERMS OF PATH LENGTHS AND CLUSTER COEFFICIENTS INDICATING THAT THE PTSD DIAGNOSED PATIENTS HAVE DIFFERENT GRAPH PROPERTIES. HOWEVER, THE DIFFERENCES BETWEEN THE GRAPHS NEEDS TO BE MORE CAREFULLY EXPLORED AND EXPANDED TO THE FULL POPULATIONS.
 
 THIS RESEARCH PLANS TO USE ADVANCED MACHINE LEARNING TECHNIQUES TO IDENTIFY BIOMARKERS IN NEUROIMAGING DATA. IN PARTICULAR, WE PLAN TO EXAMINE LINEAR ALGEBRA FORMULATIONS OF REGRESSION AND CLASSIFICATION WITH AN EMPHASIS ON SPARSITY AS A FORM OF GUIDANCE FOR INTERPRETABLE RESULTS. RESULTS WILL BE VALIDATED ON NEUROIMAGING DATA FOR WHICH PROFESSOR IAN DAVIDSON HAS THE EXPERTISE AND MOTIVATION NECESSARY TO CARRY OUT THE PROPOSED RESEARCH. HIS PARTICULAR RESEARCH EXPERTISE IS IN THE AREA OF COMPUTER SCIENCE WITH AN EMPHASIS ON MACHINE LEARNING AND DATA MINING. PROFESSOR DAVIDSON IS AN NSF CAREER GRANT AWARDEE ON THE AREA OF USING GUIDANCE IN UNSUPERVISED LEARNING ALGORITHMS AND HE HAS SPENT THE PAST FIVE YEARS WORKING ON THIS TOPIC. 
 
 WE PROPOSED TO COMPLETE THE FULL SET OF SMALL WORLD ANALYSIS PERFORMED IN EXISTING STUDIES BUT ALSO EXTEND THIS WORK IN SEVERAL DIMENSIONS TO: I) DIFFERENT GRAPHS AND II) MORE INFORMATIVE MEASURES.

subaward_description:
THE PRIMARY GOAL OF THIS STUDY IS TO GATHER INFORMATION RELATED TO ADULT CHINOOK SALMON
 AND STEELHEAD ATTRACTION AND ENTRY AT THE FOSTER DAM (FOS) ADULT FISH FACILITY (AFF). THE
 INFORMATION WILL BE USED TO IMPROVE THE EFFECTIVENESS OF AFF OPERATIONS AND TO REDUCE HOLDING
 BY PRE-SPAWN ADULT FISH IN THE FOSTER DAM TAILRACE.
 SCOPE OF WORK.
 OBJECTIVE 1): A KEY UNKNOWN IS THE COLLECTION EFFICIENCY OF THE FOSTER AFF, BUT GENERATING
 ACCURATE AND PRECISE ESTIMATES OF THE AFF CAPTURE EFFICIENCY AND OF FISH BEHAVIORS IN THE TAILRACE
 AND FISHWAY USING PASSIVE MONITORING METHODS WILL BE CHALLENGING GIVEN UNCERTAINLY ABOUT THE
 NUMBER OF FISH PRESENT IN THE TAILRACE. MONITORING WILL OCCUR DURING A RANDOMIZED BLOCK
 EXPERIMENT SIMILAR TO THE 2015 PILOT TO ALTER FISHWAY HYDRAULIC CONDITIONS (E.G., FIGURE 2;
 APPENDIX 1).  OBJECTIVE 2:
 A RANDOM SUBSET OF DIDSON IMAGERY WILL BE ANALYZED TO DETERMINE DIEL PATTERNS OF BEHAVIOR IN
 THE TAILRACE, THE MOVEMENT RATE AND DIRECTION OF ADULTS IN THE TAILRACE NEAR THE ENTRANCE, RATE OF
 APPARENT ENTRY ATTEMPTS, RATE OF ENTRIES, AND RATE OF EXIT FOR CHINOOK SALMON-SIZED ACOUSTIC
 TARGETS.

prime_award_base_transaction_description: The purpose of this Agreement is to fund research in support of the DARPA MTO in the amount of 45,000 on contract HR0011-16-2-0038.
subawardee_business_types: OTHER NOT FOR PROFIT ORGANIZATION,1862 LAND GRANT COLLEGE,EDUCATIONAL INSTITUTION,VETERINARY COLLEGE
subaward_description: UC DAVIS WILL COLLABORATE WITH STANFORD ON THE FOLLOWING TASKS: PHASE 1 TASK 1.2: ULTRA-HIGH PURITY I2 CELL FILLING AND SEALING. A UHV FILLING STATION FOR VAPOR CELLS WILL BE BUILT AND WILL INCLUDE CAPABILITIES FOR HIGH TEMPERATURE BAKING, RF SCRUBBING, AND CELL FILLING WITH VERY HIGH PURITY MOLECULAR IODINE. A KEY CAPABILITY OF OUR APPROACH IS MULTI-STAGE VAPOR DISTILLATION OF I2. THE I2 PRESSURE WILL BE OPTIMIZED TO ADDRESS CONFLICTING DEMANDS OF MINIMIZING PRESSURE BROADENING AND FREQUENCY OFFSETS, WHILE MAXIMIZING THE ABSORPTION OF THE PROBING LASER AND FLUORESCENCE DETECTION. ADVANCED METHODS FOR CELL SEALING WILL BE USED. DELIVERABLES WILL BE A REPORT OUTLINING THE BEST METHODS AND RESULTS, AND THE PRODUCTION OF AT LEAST SIX I2 VAPOR CELLS WILL BE PRODUCED THAT CAN MEET ACES PROGRAM METRICS FOR HIGH TEMPERATURE OPERATION AND LONG-TERM FREQUENCY STABILITY. MONTHS: 1-12 STANFORD 70%, UC DAVIS 30% TASK 1.3: I2 CELL CHARACTERIZATION. INITIAL MEASUREMENTS OF THE SATURATED ABSORPTION LINEWIDTH AND CONTRAST OF THE TINY I2 VAPOR CELLS FABRICATED IN TASK 1.2 WILL BE CARRIED OUT AND COMPARED THEORY SUPPORTING STABILITY GOALS. DELIVERABLES WILL BE A REPORT DETAILING THE RESULTS. MONTHS: 4-12 STANFORD 0%, UC DAVIS 100% TASK 1.5: CONSTRUCTION OF A COMPACT SATURATION SPECTROMETER WITH REPLACEABLE CELLS. WE WILL CONSTRUCT A COMPACT SPECTROMETER FOR STUDYING ALL PHASES OF THE I2 VAPOR CELL DEVELOPMENT. THIS ESSENTIAL INSTRUMENT WILL BE ASSEMBLED FROM A COMMERCIAL, TUNABLE, NARROW-LINEWIDTH, FREQUENCY-DOUBLED (532 NM) ND:YAG LASER, FOCUSING AND ISOLATION OPTICS, PHOTODETECTORS AND A LOCK-IN AMPLIFIER FOR THIRD-DERIVATIVE SPECTROSCOPY. WE WILL ALSO DEVELOP CUSTOM SERVOS FOR LOCKING THE LASER TO SATURATED ABSORPTION LINES. DELIVERABLES WILL INCLUDE SYSTEM DESIGN, PERFORMANCE CHARACTERIZATION AND RESULTS FROM SPECTROSCOPIC EVALUATIONS OF VARIOUS I2 CELLS. MONTHS: 3-5 STANFORD 40%, UC DAVIS 60% TASK 1.8: DEMONSTRATE FREQUENCY RETRACE ΔY < 10-11 AND AGING < 10-12 /DAY. WE WILL MEASURE THE FREQUENCY RETRACE (ON/OFF/ON 4/24/4 HOURS) AND AGING RATE OF THE I2 GREEN FREQUENCY STANDARD TO VERIFY THAT THE SYSTEM AND APPROACH CAN ACHIEVE THE REQUIRED ENVIRONMENTAL INSENSITIVITY ON DAY TIME SCALES (105S). MEASUREMENTS RESULTS WILL DETERMINE THE REQUIREMENTS FOR THE CONTROL SYSTEMS. WHEN PROJECTED TO LONG TIMES THE PERFORMANCE MUST BE COMMENSURATE WITH THE ULTIMATE STABILITY GOAL OF ΔY=10-13 AT ONE MONTH, WHICH WILL BE DEMONSTRATED IN PHASE-II. MONTHS: 7-12 STANFORD 80%, UC DAVIS 20% PHASE 2 TASK 2.4: SEMI-MONOLITHIC HYBRID INTEGRATION OF I2 CELL OPTICS AND DETECTORS. WE WILL DESIGN AND FABRICATE A SEMI-MONOLITHIC INTEGRATION OF THE MINIATURE VAPOR CELL, OPTICS AND DETECTION ELECTRONICS TO ENSURE THERMO-MECHANICAL STABILITY IN A SOLID STRUCTURE THAT MITIGATES NUMEROUS EFFECTS AND TECHNICAL LIMITATIONS RELATED TO THERMALLY-DRIVEN CHANGES IN GEOMETRY. SUCH EFFECTS INCLUDE OPTICAL INTERFERENCE, SCATTERED LIGHT, BEAM MISALIGNMENT, POLARIZATION AND CHANGES DETECTOR PERFORMANCE. THE HYBRID INTEGRATED I2 SYSTEM WILL BE SMALL ENOUGH THAT IT CAN MEET ACES SWAP REQUIREMENTS IN FUTURE INTEGRATION INTO COMPLETE CLOCK. MONTHS: 6-12 STANFORD 40%, UC DAVIS 60% TASK 2.5: IMPLEMENT CONTROL SYSTEMS. MEASUREMENTS FROM PHASE-I WILL GUIDE THE DESIGN OF CONTROL SYSTEMS THAT ARE REQUIRED TO MITIGATE RESIDUAL FREQUENCY SHIFTS THAT DEPEND UPON CONTROLLABLE ENVIRONMENTAL FACTORS INCLUDING: TEMPERATURE, OPTICAL POWER, BEAM GEOMETRY, LASER AM AND FM NOISE, MODULATION AND DETECTION METHODS, RESIDUAL AMPLITUDE MODULATION, AND ELECTRONIC PHASE SHIFTS. DELIVERABLES WILL INCLUDE DATA CHARACTERIZING THE VARIATIONS, CONTROL STRATEGIES TO AMELIORATE THEM AND CIRCUIT DESIGNS AND VERIFICATIONS.
